# Kconfig — Ornet Kernel Module Configuration
#
# Integrates with the Linux kernel's menuconfig system.
# Source this from the kernel's Kconfig or include as
# an external module configuration.
#
# Usage in kernel Kconfig:
#   source "drivers/char/ornet/Kconfig"

config ORNET
	tristate "Revo OS Ornet — Kernel-Native AI Inference"
	depends on X86_64
	depends on MODULES
	select VMALLOC
	help
	  Ornet is Revo OS's kernel-level AI inference subsystem.
	  It provides a character device (/dev/ornet) for zero-copy
	  IPC between userspace inference clients and kernel-resident
	  language models.

	  This module includes:
	    - Model Memory Manager (vmalloc + page pinning)
	    - Lock-free ring buffer (SPSC, 4 × 4KB pages)
	    - GGUF model loading via ioctl

	  If unsure, say N.

config ORNET_DEBUG
	bool "Ornet debug output"
	depends on ORNET
	default n
	help
	  Enable verbose debug logging for the Ornet module.
	  Includes ring buffer state dumps, page pinning
	  statistics, and model loading progress.

	  This adds ~2 KB to the module size. Say N for
	  production use.

config ORNET_MODEL_PATH
	string "Auto-load model path"
	depends on ORNET
	default ""
	help
	  Path to a GGUF model file to load automatically
	  when the ornet module is inserted. Leave empty
	  to load manually via ioctl after boot.

	  Example: /revo/ai/models/ornith-1.0-9b-Q4_K_M.gguf

config ORNET_RING_SLOTS
	int "Ring buffer slots"
	depends on ORNET
	default 64
	range 16 256
	help
	  Number of slots in the request and response rings.
	  More slots = higher throughput under burst load,
	  but more memory. Each slot is 64 bytes.
	  Default: 64 (4 KB ring pages).
